{
  "texts": [
    "We exclude simple mentions of landmarks, such as 'the White House', unless they are accompanied by an address (e.g., 'The White House, 1600 Pennsylvania Avenue NW, Washington, DC' or even simply 'The White House, Washington DC').",
    "This is to ensure we don't count documents that mention landmarks in passing, although we recognise it can be argued that LLMs may learn the physical world from such examples as well.We do not discriminate against real and fictional addresses.",
    "For example, we count '123 Main Street<br/>New York, NY 10001' as a valid address even though we are certain it is used as a filler.",
    "Similarly, we do not check if latitude-longitude pairs are valid as long as it is clear the pair of numbers represents physical coordinates.",
    "We do, however, exclude the coordinates of the Null Island (0,0) as those are often used for map initialisation and are not meaningful otherwise [16]."
  ]
}